install tmux and begin a new session
> sudo apt-get update
> apt-get install -y tmux
> tmux

split a pane vertically:
> Ctrl-b %

split a pane horizonally:
> Ctrl-b "

switch pane:
> Ctrl-b o

list all commands:
> Ctrl-b ?

Scroll:
> Ctrl-b [ 
then you can use your normal navigation keys to scroll around (eg. Up Arrow or PgDn). Press q to quit scroll mode.

ref:
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-and-use-tmux-on-ubuntu-12-10--2
https://gist.github.com/andreyvit/2921703 [cheatsheet]
http://superuser.com/questions/209437/how-do-i-scroll-in-tmux
https://mutelight.org/practical-tmux

